 <name>Heimdall</name>
 <summary>Flash firmware onto Samsung mobile devices</summary>

 <description>
   <p>
     Heimdall is a cross-platform open-source tool suite, used to flash
     firmware (aka ROMs) onto Samsung mobile devices. It is an alternative
     to the official, but proprietary Odin utility.
   </p>
   <p>
     Assuming a mobile device is put into "Download Mode" (also known as
     "Odin Mode"), Heimdall will connect to the device over USB. This should
     work with most devices, but there is no guarentee that it will.
   </p>
   <p>
     Flashing operations are irreversable and may invalidate a device's
     waranties. Use this tool at your own risk.
   </p>
   <p>
     Heimdall is maintained and predominantly developed by Glass Echidna, a
     tiny independent software development company.
   </p>
 </description>

